The paper introduces a novel framework for reservoir computing using cellular automata, which is a topic related to neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE). The use of cellular automata as the reservoir of dynamical systems also relates to the field of dynamical systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the efficiency and computational complexity of the proposed framework, which is relevant to the field of machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of Boolean operations for concept building and symbolic processing relates to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control theory (cs.SY).
